  "title": "PROJECT ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles &amp; Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee site activities to ensure construction progress aligns with project schedules and specifications.</li>\n  <li>Interpret and review construction drawings, ensuring compliance with design plans and standards.</li>\n  <li>Monitor workmanship and materials to meet regulatory and project quality requirements.</li>\n  <li>Enforce workplace health and safety regulations, conducting site inspections to ensure compliance.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with clients, subcontractors, and consultants to resolve technical and operational issues.</li>\n  <li>Assist in managing project budgets, tracking expenses, and ensuring cost-effectiveness.</li>\n  <li>Maintain accurate site records, progress reports, and necessary documentation per ISO standards.</li>\n  <li>Identify and address construction challenges, providing timely solutions to keep the project on track.</li>\n  <li>Any other duties assigned by the company from time to time.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n  <li>PEB recognised Bachelor’s degree in Civil Engineering.</li>\n  <li>Minimum <strong>5 years</strong> of experience in construction project management or a similar role.</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of construction methods, materials, and regulations.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in project management software (e.g., MS Project, AutoCAD).</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication, organizational, and problem-solving skills.</li>\n  <li>Ability to work under pressure and manage multiple tasks simultaneously.</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of health and safety regulations and practices.</li>\n</ul>",
